🔑 Why HashMap is Used?

Without HashMap:
Searching in array → O(n)

With HashMap:
Searching by key → O(1)

That’s why HashMap is heavily used in DSA + interviews.

Roll Number → Student Name
101 → Rahul
102 → Aman
103 → Neha

Here:
Key = Roll Number
Value = Student Name


HashMap Syntax:  HashMap<KeyType, ValueType> map = new HashMap<>();
Example:         HashMap<Integer, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();


🧑‍💻 Basic HashMap Operations
1️⃣ Put (Insert)
        map.put(1, 10);
        map.put(2, 20);
2️⃣ Get (Retrieve)
        int val = map.get(1);   // 10
3️⃣ Contains Key
        map.containsKey(2);  // true
4️⃣ Remove
        map.remove(1);

🔹 getOrDefault() (VERY IMPORTANT)
map.getOrDefault(key, defaultValue);

🔹 Iterating a HashMap
1️⃣ Using Entry Set (BEST)
for (Map.Entry<Integer, Integer> entry : map.entrySet()) {
    System.out.println(entry.getKey() + " -> " + entry.getValue());
}

2️⃣ Using Key Set
for (int key : map.keySet()) {
    System.out.println(key + " -> " + map.get(key));
}

🔹 HashMap with Characters (String Problems)
String s = "aabbcc";
HashMap<Character, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();

for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
    map.put(c, map.getOrDefault(c, 0) + 1);
}

### methods

put()           → insert / update
get()           → fetch value
getOrDefault()  → safe get ⭐
containsKey()   → key exists?
entrySet()      → best iteration ⭐
remove()        → delete